<b>Forum Permissions:</b><br />
By default, users will have the permissions for their usergroup (see the <a href="usergroup.php?do=modify" target="_blank">Usergroup Manager</a>) in each forum.  However, you might not want users of a particular usergroup to have access to every forum.  In that case, vBulletin allows you to create custom permissions for a specific forum for a specific usergroup.  This is useful in restricting certain forums for certain usergroups.